spans.text: Be dumb , sweet Choristers , I heed you not
yonder leafy grove , Indulgent bliss there waits you
high the senseless roar Of laughter , and pale woe , abashed , retires
mine , once past the quivering lip
how bright she painted future scenes
all the piles of bliss gay Hope
The reasoner raves , Lifts the hard eye , and with long-winded speech , And self-applauding dialect
OH you ! whose spirits rove beyond yonder orbs , To find the realms of rest , for such there are , To prove a home when the sad soul shall need it
upheld By brilliant Fancy's rapture-giving wing
the realms of rest , for such there are , To prove a home when the sad soul shall need it
a home when the sad soul shall need it
the group of anxious souls Searching the path to rest
of anxious souls Searching the path to rest
no other way can ever be found , And then consigns them over to endless woe
